"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="574" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824695?width=860&amp;height=574" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">周三，人们在首尔测试了三星新款可折叠智能手机。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：KIM HONG-JI/REUTERS </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001084855"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jiyoung-sohn" itemprop="url" rel="author">孙智英</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 27 日凌晨 2:07（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/samsung-galaxy-fold-flip-smartphones-launch-52f9b868"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>首尔——<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/SSNHZ" class="company-name">三星电子</a>决定首次在本国推出其最新的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/samsung-echoes-apples-smartphone-strategy-with-expanded-new-lineup-11550691001?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">折叠手机</a>，而不是在另一个外国城市，反映出这家全球最大智能手机制造商的命运分化。</p><p>从好的方面来说，韩国消费者已经接受了这些小玩意儿，它们像一本书一样打开到更大的屏幕上，或者像蛤蜊一样弯成两半。缺点是他们是世界上唯一大量这样做的人。</p><p>周三在首尔举行的发布会展示了大屏幕 Galaxy Z Fold 5 和更紧凑的 Galaxy Z Flip 5，它们拥有升级的相机、处理器和耐用性。前几年，<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/SSNHZ" class="company-name">三星</a>在其最大的市场（从纽约到巴塞罗那，从旧金山到柏林）举办了旗舰发布会。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="400" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=6D61E442-8682-4CC6-B6EF-416253790290&amp;height=400&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;resetOnComplete=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fsamsung-galaxy-fold-flip-smartphones-launch-52f9b868&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">谷歌 Pixel 和三星 Galaxy 等可折叠手机提供了更多的屏幕空间。但它们价格昂贵、体积庞大且易碎。 《华尔街日报》的妮可·阮 (Nicole Nguyen) 分析了其利弊。照片：贾斯汀·沙利文/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>“我们实际上是在改变移动体验的剧本，”三星移动业务营销主管斯蒂芬妮·崔(Stephanie Choi)表示。她在首尔市中心的发布会上向人群发表了讲话，其中包括韩国男孩组合 BTS 的一名成员。</p><p>当 2019 年推出第一代机型时，三星宣称可折叠显示屏手机是一项突破性创新，将开启“移动历史的全新篇章”。但该公司押注这些手机可以通过推动<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AAPL" class="">苹果</a>iPhone<span class="company-name-type">所</span>缺乏的硬件进步来维持（如果不是扩大的话）其高端用户群，但迄今为止尚未成功。</p><p>如今，三星<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/googles-pixel-fold-folding-phones-are-starting-to-make-sense-a2796976?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在可折叠智能手机领域处于领先地位</a>，占去年全球 1420 万部可折叠智能手机出货量的 80% 以上，其余大部分来自中国智能手机品牌。科技市场研究机构 Canalys 表示，尽管可折叠手机市场在增长，但规模仍然很小，到 2023 年将占全球智能手机出货量的 1%。</p><p>三星在更广泛的高端智能手机市场的份额正在萎缩。 Canalys 的数据显示，到 2022 年底，其在全球售价 600 美元及以上智能手机市场的份额较 2019 年下降 9 个百分点至 16%。与此同时，苹果的份额从 59% 增长到 72%。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823238?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">谷歌 Android 工程副总裁戴夫·伯克 (Dave Burke) 演示 Pixel Fold 手机。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：大卫·保罗·莫里斯/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>苹果尚未宣布任何可折叠手机的计划，但过去曾<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/smartphone-makers-gamble-that-they-know-when-to-fold-em-11551701247?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">探索过折叠设计</a>。苹果没有回应置评请求。</p><p>三星发言人表示，该公司仍全力致力于可折叠产品领域。她表示，除了国内市场外，三星在欧洲、中国和西南亚的可折叠手机年销量也在不断增长，已经超过了 Galaxy Note 系列。她指的是该品牌现已停产的大屏幕手机，这些手机长期以来一直是该公司夏季推出的旗舰产品。</p><p>三星还指出，科技市场研究公司 Counterpoint Research 的新数据预计，到 2027 年，可折叠手机设备的需求将超过 1 亿台。Counterpoint 对 3,000 人进行了调查，结果显示，美国、中国和韩国约 55% 的智能手机用户表示愿意购买可折叠设备作为他们的下一部手机。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div id="buyside-sector" class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>从华尔街日报探索买方</h4><p>有关产品和服务的专家推荐，独立于《华尔街日报》新闻编辑室。</p><ul class="articleList"><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/buyside/electronics/google-pixel-tablet-review-4fab4ee9?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">Google Pixel 平板电脑是第一款吸引评论者注意力的 Android 平板电脑</a></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/buyside/electronics/best-smartwatch-5f063383?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">适合每个手腕的 5 款最佳智能手表</a></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/buyside/electronics/best-power-bank-01664892024?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">最适合您手机的 4 款移动电源</a></li></ul></div></div><p>Counterpoint 驻首尔总监 Tom Kang 表示，购买可折叠手机需要多次“信念的飞跃”。消费者必须花更多的钱—— <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/samsung-galaxy-new-smartphone-11660102404?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">去年的 Galaxy Z Fold</a>机型售价约为 1,800 美元， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iphone-14-and-14-pro-review-go-pro-or-go-home-11663160540?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">几乎是 iPhone 14 Pro 的两倍</a>——购买一款配备摄像头和类似或稍低规格功能的智能手机，以换取折叠时更大或更紧凑的新型显示屏。</p><p>妮可·彭（Nicole Peng）表示，就目前的情况而言，可折叠设备缺乏专门的“杀手级应用程序”，也没有比传统智能手机具有压倒性的优势，因此其高价是合理的。</p> Canalys 驻香港高级副总裁。因此，可折叠手机并不是“人们选择新型高端智能手机的首选”，她补充道。<p></p><p>但在几项全球调查中，消费者对购买可折叠设备的兴趣日益浓厚，尽管他们希望价格下降。</p><p>唯一的亮点是韩国，去年可折叠手机占该国智能手机出货量的 14%。据 Counterpoint 称，这是全球所有主要市场中采用最广泛的市场，可折叠手机仅占美国和欧洲智能手机总出货量的 2%。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823240?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">上海的人们走过 Vivo 展示的数字画作，以宣传其可折叠手机。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Cfoto/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>行业分析师表示，三星之所以能取得这一成功，是因为其拥有强大的品牌忠诚度，以及运营商提供的大幅折扣，帮助消费者转向可折叠设备。他们表示，这种策略可以在其他地方复制，以推动更多可折叠产品的采用，尽管这可能会削弱盈利能力。</p><p>可折叠手机，包括三星的手机，通常有两种类型。较小的型号折叠起来后可以变成传统智能手机大小的一半，以满足优先考虑便携性的买家的需求。还可以在覆盖手机一部分的第二个外部屏幕上阅读消息或其他警报。他们还允许用户在坐姿半打开手机的情况下自拍或观看视频。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>更大、更昂贵的可折叠显示屏型号在打开时变成了平板电脑的大小，并提供各种多任务功能和利用更大屏幕的独特功能。当关闭时，第二个外部屏幕覆盖了大部分外部，其工作原理与标准智能手机类似。</p><p>价格与去年的型号保持不变：Galaxy Z Flip 5 的零售价约为 1,000 美元，Galaxy Z Fold 5 的零售价约为 1,800 美元。周三在美国和韩国等部分市场开始预订。这些手机于 8 月 11 日上架。</p><p>对于新推出的尺寸较小的 Galaxy Z Flip 5，手机合上时使用的外部屏幕比前一年的型号大了近四倍。现在对角线长度为 3.4 英寸。更宽的显示屏使使用后置摄像头更容易自拍，同时提供更广泛的免提拍摄选项。手机完全打开时的对角线尺寸为 6.7 英寸。</p><p> Galaxy Z Fold 5 的尺寸与之前的版本大致相同，打开时显示屏为 7.6 英寸，外屏为独立的 6.2 英寸。新型号提供增强的多任务功能。</p><p>然而，随着越来越多的品牌进入这一领域，可折叠智能手机正在成为一个更大的战场。 Oppo、华为、小米和Vivo等<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/huaweis-foldable-smartphone-raises-the-barand-price-tag-11551021269?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国品牌</a>都推出了可折叠机型。今年早些时候，谷歌推出了首款可折叠智能手机 Pixel Fold，称其为美国最薄的可折叠手机，价格与三星 Galaxy Z Fold 4 相似。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>你会购买三星的折叠手机吗？为什么或者为什么不？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>对于三星来说，可折叠手机领域的更多竞争是一把双刃剑。它可以扩大该类别并提高供应链的效率，从而降低相关零部件的成本。不断增长的竞争对手领域也增加了对折叠显示器的需求，这对三星来说是一个推动因素，因为它也是一家显示器制造商。与此同时，竞争对手可能会削弱三星目前的主导地位。</p><p> Canalys 预计，今年全球可折叠手机出货量将增长至 2500 万部，但由于更多品牌推出可折叠手机，三星的份额预计将下降至约 60% 至 65%。</p><p> “随着越来越多的竞争对手加入，问题将不仅仅是销量的增长，而是三星能否继续在可折叠设备领域保持‘领先’？”彭说。</p><p>写信给 Jiyoung Sohn，邮箱为<a href="mailto:jiyoung.sohn@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jiyoung.sohn@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/d90969df-db3f-4890-9f4e-2892f502493a.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 06:07:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/samsung-galaxy-fold-flip-smartphones-launch-52f9b868</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/samsung-galaxy-fold-flip-smartphones-launch-52f9b868<author><![CDATA[Jiyoung Sohn]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>计算机/消费电子产品</category><category>电信设备</category><category>个人电子产品</category><category>音视频设备</category><category>手机/移动电话</category><category>消费品</category><category>耐用家居产品</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>移动设备</category><category>家用电子/电器</category><category>技术</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>生活/生活方式</category><category>个人技术</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>三星电子</category><category>005930.SE</category><category> KR:005930</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>活的</category><category>生活方式</category><category>个人技术</category><category>电脑</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>电信设备</category><category>个人电子产品</category><category>声音的</category><category>视频设备</category><category>细胞</category><category>手机</category><category>消费品</category><category>耐用家用产品</category><category>移动设备</category><category>家用电子产品</category><category>电器</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Netflix Reworks Microsoft Pact and Lowers Ad Prices]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Streamer 尝试推出每月 6.99 美元的广告套餐，需要耐心等待<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001087483"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823606?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Netflix 正在探索让广告商更容易、更便宜地购买广告空间的方法。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Gene J. Puskar/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001087483"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/suzanne-vranica" itemprop="url" rel="author">Suzanne Vranica</a></span> 、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jessica-toonkel" itemprop="url" rel="author">Jessica Toonkel</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/patience-haggin" itemprop="url" rel="author">Patience Haggin</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 27 日上午 12:01 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-reworks-microsoft-pact-lowers-ad-prices-in-bid-for-growth-159b359a"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>在与<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MSFT" class="company-name">微软</a>达成协议一年后， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NFLX" class="company-name">Netflix</a>正在重组其<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-partners-with-microsoft-to-launch-advertising-supported-plan-11657738975?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">广告合作伙伴</a>关系，并降低广告价格，以推动其业务的这一新兴领域的发展。</p><p>这家流媒体公司去年为消费者推出了每月 6.99 美元的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-ads-plan-streaming-business-11659538834?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">广告支持选项</a>。微软赢得了为该服务提供技术并代表 Netflix 销售广告的竞争，部分原因是它愿意支付“收入保证”，承诺向 Netflix 提供大量资金。</p><p>知情人士称，随着新的广告层级慢慢获得关注，Netflix 已初步讨论通过除微软之外的其他合作伙伴销售广告。 Netflix 正在修改与微软的协议，以减少收入保证。这些条款仍在敲定中。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=0B69A51F-2148-4479-9D5B-1AB9ABE390DC&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fnetflix-reworks-microsoft-pact-lowers-ad-prices-in-bid-for-growth-159b359a&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Netflix 联席首席执行官泰德·萨兰多斯 (Ted Sarandos) 最近表示，该公司和其他流媒体平台、工作室和网络“非常致力于”与好莱坞知名演员和编剧达成协议。照片：克里斯·德尔马斯/法新社/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>与此同时，Netflix 正在为广告商提供更好的优惠。据广告买家称，在最近的广告交易中，一些广告商同意为每 1000 名观众支付大约 39 至 45 美元。据《华尔街日报》报道，Netflix 此前向一些品牌收取了 45 至 55 美元左右的费用。</p><p>结合起来，重新制定的微软协议和更低的价格可能会吸引此前一直持观望态度的 Netflix 新广告商。</p><p>去年夏天，Netflix 选择微软作为其广告合作伙伴，而不是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GOOG" class="">Alphabet</a>旗下的谷歌和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/CMCSA" class="">康卡斯特</a><span class="company-name-type">，</span> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/with-netflix-ad-deal-microsoft-makes-a-splash-on-madison-avenue-11657916701?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">这让麦迪逊大道感到惊讶</a><span class="company-name-type">。</span>据《华尔街日报》报道，作为两家公司最初协议的一部分，Netflix 获得了“最低保证”，即承诺将获得大量广告收入以限制其财务风险。</p><p>一些知情人士表示，一些 Netflix 高管对微软没有出售更多广告库存感到沮丧。一位知情人士表示，销售疲软和弱于预期的广告市场迄今为止导致微软支付了一年前 Netflix 选择微软作为其推出广告业务合作伙伴时同意的担保规定的最高金额。</p><p>一些广告买家表示，Netflix 提供的较低费率与其他一些订阅视频服务的收费更加一致，吸引了新的广告商从 Netflix 购买广告。</p><p> Netflix 首席财务官斯宾塞·诺依曼</p>上周表示，该公司的广告收入并不重要，他预计今年不会成为主要贡献者。自推出每月 6.99 美元的广告支持计划以来，Netflix 高管表示将采取循序渐进的方式扩展业务。<p></p><p>尽管增加了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-nflx-q2-earnings-report-2023-92a620c8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">近 600 万订户</a>，但 Netflix 公布的第二季度营收未达到预期，导致该公司股价上周暴跌。尽管 Netflix 是盈利的， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tvs-golden-era-proved-costly-to-streamers-87353c61?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">但与许多竞争对手不同</a>，它的收入增长在拥挤的流媒体市场中已经放缓。</p><p>摩根士丹利分析师本杰明·斯温伯恩在最近给投资者的一份报告中表示，一段时间以来，人们对 Netflix 广告业务快速增长的预期过于乐观。他写道，Netflix 的广告业务目前对该公司的收入并不重要，吸引订户加入广告支持计划还需要时间，尽管从长远来看，销售广告可能有助于公司更快增长。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>根据订阅分析公司 Antenna 的数据，截至 6 月底，广告层占 Netflix 美国订阅用户的 3.3%，高于 3 月底的 1.7%。</p><p> Netflix 高管表示，广告层为每位用户带来的平均收入高于其 15.49 美元的标准计划。广告买家和分析师预计，Netflix 限制密码共享并终止向美国和英国新客户提供<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-scraps-its-cheapest-ad-free-plan-aea36bb7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">9.99 美元基本无广告服务的</a>举措将促使消费者签署更便宜、有广告支持的套餐。</p><p>该公司在春季销售广告套餐，时间是在“前期”季节，广告商传统上承诺在下一季购买电视节目的商业时间。许多广告商对 Netflix 进入广告业务表示欢迎，因为他们长期以来一直无法接触到观看该流媒体热门娱乐节目的用户。</p><p>根据收视公司尼尔森的数据，6 月份 Netflix 占据了美国电视观看时间的 8.2%，在流媒体服务中所占份额仅次于谷歌的 YouTube。</p><p>一些广告买家采取谨慎态度。据一些知情人士透露，由于 Netflix 广告层的用户数量有限，一家代表主要品牌的广告购买机构预计将减少其前期广告承诺的规模。一位知情人士表示，随着订户基数的增长，该机构将在临近广告投放时间时购买额外的 Netflix 广告空间。</p><p> Netflix 广告层的订阅者数量相对较少，这使得广告商很难在该平台上投入大量资金。广告买家表示，品牌面临的风险是观众过于频繁地看到他们的广告，并且无法有效地瞄准大量特定的订阅者群体。广告买家表示，因此，许多品牌只在这项服务上花费了数百万美元，一些较大的交易在 600 万至 800 万美元之间。</p><p>相比之下，大型广告商往往承诺在电视前期广告销售季节花费数千万美元。</p><p>与其他媒体公司一样，Netflix 在 6 月份在法国里维埃拉举办的戛纳国际创意节广告节期间招待了财力雄厚的广告商。</p><p>据广告买家称，Netflix 要求品牌保持耐心，因为广告业务仍在发展。</p><p>除了降低费率之外，Netflix 还在探索让广告商更容易购买广告空间的方法。</p><p>知情人士称，虽然广告商目前必须通过 Netflix 或其合作伙伴微软进行购买，但这家流媒体公司已与 Trade Desk 和康卡斯特旗下 FreeWheel 等广告科技公司就允许他们出售 Netflix 广告空间进行了初步讨论。在这种情况下，微软的 Xandr 将继续发挥作用，包括提供为观众看到的广告提供服务的技术。</p><p>一些公司在经济不确定的情况下削减<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/advertising-slowdown-spreads-beyond-tech-giants-to-hit-tv-networks-publishers-11659846058?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">广告支出</a>，这对广告市场造成了打击。广告公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/IPG" class="company-name">Interpublic Group</a> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/stock-market-today-dow-jones-07-21-2023/card/interpublic-group-stock-drops-on-lower-2023-outlook-ZuOJqzGWQoYBLNMtt0Cg?mod=Searchresults_pos1&amp;page=1&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">下调 2023 年增长预期</a>后，该公司股价周五暴跌。该公司表示，继此前预测今年有机收入增长 2% 至 4% 后，现在预计有机收入增长 1% 至 2%。</p><p>广告商也对广告费用持谨慎态度，因为他们<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/streaming-brought-hollywood-to-a-standstill-now-comes-the-pain-3afcbb68?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">担心演员和编剧的罢工</a>——好莱坞 60 年来最大的劳工行动——将如何影响市场，新的广播节目将暂停和重播，而真人秀节目预计将在秋季节目中占据重要地位。广告买家表示，Netflix 等流媒体公司可能会从长期罢工中受益。</p><p>尽管广告市场疲软，Netflix 联席首席执行官格雷格·彼得斯 (Greg Peters) 在上周与分析师举行的财报电话会议上表示，“看到了良好的需求和前期的良好进展”。</p><p>写信给 Suzanne Vranica ( <a href="mailto:Suzanne.Vranica@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Suzanne.Vranica@wsj.com)</a> 、Jessica Toonkel ( <a href="mailto:jessica.toonkel@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jessica.toonkel@wsj.com</a> ) 和 Patience Haggin ( <a href="mailto:patience.haggin@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">patience.haggin@wsj.com</a> ) </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/751c4a60-884a-4f29-9ce6-db91fbb92c01.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 04:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-reworks-microsoft-pact-lowers-ad-prices-in-bid-for-growth-159b359a</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-reworks-microsoft-pact-lowers-ad-prices-in-bid-for-growth-159b359a<author><![CDATA[Suzanne VranicaJessica ToonkelPatience Haggin]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>专有的</category><category>计算机/消费电子产品</category><category>软件</category><category>应用软件</category><category>广告服务</category><category>多媒体内容服务</category><category>广告/营销/公共关系</category><category>商业/消费者服务</category><category>计算</category><category>媒体内容分发</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>营销服务</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>流媒体服务</category><category>技术</category><category>企业战略/规划</category><category>所有权变更</category><category>收购/合并/持股</category><category>营销</category><category>价格</category><category>广告</category><category>合同/订单</category><category>非政府合同/订单</category><category>企业行动</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>市场/营销</category><category>企业组织架构重组</category><category>伙伴关系/合作</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>埃培智集团 (Interpublic Group)</category><category> IPG</category><category>微软</category><category>微软公司</category><category>Netflix</category><category> NFLX</category><category>企业战略</category><category>规划</category><category>所有权变更</category><category>收购</category><category>合并</category><category>持股</category><category>营销</category><category>价格</category><category>广告</category><category>合同</category><category>命令</category><category>非政府合同</category><category>企业行动</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>市场</category><category>企业组织架构调整</category><category>伙伴关系</category><category>合作</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>电脑</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>软件</category><category>应用软件</category><category>广告服务</category><category>多媒体内容服务</category><category>公共关系</category><category>商业</category><category>消费服务</category><category>计算</category><category>媒体内容分发</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>营销服务</category><category>媒体</category><category>娱乐</category><category>流媒体服务</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Elon Musk’s X Rebrand Cues Complications—and Porn Jokes]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Twitter最新的剧变激怒了前员工，可能引发商标之争<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823469/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="周一，当 Twitter（或 X）的品牌更名首次出现在社交媒体平台上时，用户感到很困惑。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>周一，当 Twitter（或 X）的品牌更名首次出现在社交媒体平台上时，用户感到很困惑。乔纳森·布雷迪/祖玛出版社<span>乔纳森·布雷迪/祖玛出版社</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001085735"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001085735"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/talal-ansari" itemprop="url" rel="author">Talal Ansari</a></span> 、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/meghan-bobrowsky" itemprop="url" rel="author">Meghan Bobrowsky</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/alyssa-lukpat" itemprop="url" rel="author">​​Alyssa Lukpat</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 26 日晚上 7:49（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musk-twitter-x-rebrand-trademark-bird-logo-b7433fb6"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/elon-musk">埃隆·马斯克 (Elon Musk</a> ) 的 Twitter 品牌重塑一开始就很混乱。</p><p>将蓝鸟标志换成字母 X 让<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musks-pivot-to-x-draws-strong-opinions-across-twitter-5bc80833?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">用户感到困惑</a>，让一些前员工感到不安，并为诉讼打开了大门。放弃网站的命名法会威胁到多年的品牌资产。有人说，新标志更像是色情网站，而不是社交媒体平台。</p><p>这一切都是因为马斯克对字母 X 的持久执着。</p><p>这位世界首富已经公开表示，他希望将 X 变成一款所谓的“一切应用程序”，提供从音频和视频到消息传递和银行业务的各种功能。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>您如何看待 Twitter 的新 X 品牌？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> “我喜欢字母 X，”马斯克周日在<a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1683053326097588224?s=20" target="_blank" class="icon none">推</a>特上发了一条他用手臂写字母 X 的照片。</p><p> X.com 是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musk-revives-old-banking-dream-in-pursuing-250-billion-twitter-valuation-88289aba?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">马斯克在线支付公司</a>在更名为<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/PYPL" class="">PayPal</a>之前的名称<span class="company-name-type">。</span>然后是马斯克的火箭公司SpaceX，由这位亿万富翁在二十多年前创立。他的新<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musk-xai-artificial-intelligence-company-openai-chatgpt-4a6f178a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">人工智能项目</a>被称为 xAI。马斯克经常把他的一个<span class="company-name-type">孩子</span>称为“X”。他的电动汽车公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TSLA" class="">特斯拉</a>将其一款汽车称为“Model X”。</p><p> Twitter（或 X）没有回应置评请求。</p><p>律师表示，对马斯克来说，改变一封信在公众意识中的含义可能是一项挑战，尤其是那些带有下流联想的信件。 X 级一词通常被理解为指成人内容。许多色情网站的名称和徽标中都包含字母 X。</p><p>色情网站 XVideos 周日在该网站（前身为 Twitter）上向马斯克表示感谢。 “我们喜欢看到 Xvideos 流行。谢谢@elonmusk，”帖子中<a href="https://twitter.com/xvideoscom/status/1683202798564036609?s=20" target="_blank" class="icon none">写道</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=0F91130A-ED9D-497B-A282-F26CCCF5DD91&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Felon-musk-twitter-x-rebrand-trademark-bird-logo-b7433fb6&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">周一，在该平台所有者埃隆·马斯克(Elon Musk)在一系列推文中宣布这一消息后，许多用户的标志性蓝鸟标志变成了“X”。这一变化是在 Twitter 品牌重塑之际发生的。照片：阿兰·乔卡德/法新社/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>一些 Twitter 前员工在 LinkedIn 账户上看到一个新的黑白 X 时感到震惊。</p><p>在 Twitter 工作了 12 年的萨拉·贝克普尔 (Sara Beykpour) 在 Twitter 上发布了一张带有 X 标志的 LinkedIn 个人资料照片，并表示：“不想。 @LinkedIn 请帮忙。”她拒绝发表评论。</p><p>尼克·麦康奈尔 (Nic McConnell) 曾于 2018 年至 2020 年担任 Twitter 客户经理，周一在他的个人资料中出现黑白 X 后，他向 LinkedIn 寻求帮助。</p><p> “我不想以任何身份与埃隆·马斯克有任何联系，而且我确信我从来没有为任何 X 工作过，”他在 LinkedIn 上的一篇公开帖子中写道。两个小时内，他个人资料上的徽标恢复为鸟。</p><p>麦康奈尔表示，在推特工作对他的职业生涯有帮助。 “我不知道如果我的简历上有 X，是否还会有这样的机会。”</p><p> LinkedIn 没有回应置评请求。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/58020bf4-c05e-49a7-9600-0bcf306cf602.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>品牌重塑不仅仅可以激怒前员工。这可能会给 X Corp 带来法律挑战。该公司不拥有在社交媒体上使用字母 X 的权利。</p><p>纽约 Poler Legal LLC 律师事务所的商标诉讼律师艾米丽·波勒 (Emily Poler) 表示：“Twitter 不能只是阻止世界其他地方将这封信用于其他用途。”</p><p>商标律师表示，保护潜在商标或抵御有关 X 使用的诉讼可能是一场漫长的战斗。商标律师乔什·格本 (Josh Gerben) 表示，在全球范围内注册 X 商标可能需要花费超过 1 亿美元，并向其他商标持有人支付和解费用。</p><p>据美国专利商标局称，美国有数千个与字母 X 相关的商标。 《华尔街日报》没有发现 X 公司注册任何 X 商标。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/META" class="company-name">Meta Platforms</a>拥有其中一个商标：用于社交网络的蓝白 X 徽标。梅塔拒绝发表评论。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musk-says-twitter-will-change-its-logo-to-x-5f73c349?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">周一，当社交媒体平台上首次出现</a>更名的消息时，Twitter（或 X）用户感到困惑。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="448" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824050?width=700&amp;height=448" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 2000 年，Peter Thiel 和 Elon Musk 与 PayPal 标志合影。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Paul Sakuma/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>“为什么要杀鸟？”一位用户发帖。</p><p> “我不明白，”多名用户写道。</p><p>其他人发帖称，该公司的新 X 徽标类似于编码器使用的字母 X 的 Unicode 字符。</p><p>主题标签#GoodbyeTwitter 和#RIPTwitter 本周在该平台上流行。</p><p>即使是参观该公司旧金山总部的访客也会对该公司的名称感到困惑。周一，工人们停止拆除大楼的推特标牌，只剩下最后两个字母“呃”。</p><p>马斯克和 X Corp. 的高管表示，该公司的改版扩大了该网站的吸引力。 “X 将成为一个可以提供一切的平台，”首席执行官琳达·亚卡里诺 (Linda Yaccarino) 在<a href="https://twitter.com/lindayacc/status/1683214311957594113" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">周日的一篇文章</a>中说道。</p><p>该公司现在必须废除 Twitter 上的口语，如“tweet”和“retweet”。马斯克<a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1683055552404897792?s=20" target="_blank" class="icon none">表示，为了回答用户的问题，帖子现在将被称为“X”</a> 。另一位用户询问现在的转发叫什么。 “整个概念应该重新考虑，”马斯克<a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1683369794760761345?s=20" target="_blank" class="icon none">说</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="1019" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823468?width=639&amp;height=1019" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">周一，工作人员停止拆除推特旧金山总部的标牌。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔什·埃德森/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>商标律师格本表示，对于像 X Corp.（前身为 Twitter）这样的公司来说，放弃其全球知名品牌而转而使用新品牌的做法并不寻常。</p><p> “你知道有多少品牌能及时到达这个时间点并具有这种国际价值，然后就把它扔到窗外吗？”格本说道。 “这真是令人瞠目结舌。”</p><p>还有其他并发症。直到周二，公司的官方账号仍然是@Twitter。 @X 句柄由其他人拥有。</p><p>旧金山 52 岁的摄影师 Gene Hwang 说，他几年前就抓住了这个用户名，因为他中间的首字母是 X。周二，Hwang 说他收到了一封来自公司的电子邮件，为他分配了一个不同的用户名，为公司释放了@X。</p><p>黄说他对事态的转变感到非常好笑。 《华尔街日报》看到的一封电子邮件显示，X 允许他将自己的帐户转移到任何未使用的用户名、商品，并允许他访问 X 的总部。</p><p>他说他正在考虑这个提议：“我不妨买点东西。”</p><p> <em>—Alexa Corse 和 Joseph De Avila 对本文做出了贡献。</em></p><p>写信给 Talal Ansari（ <a href="mailto:talal.ansari@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">talal.ansari@wsj.com</a> ）、Meghan Bobrowsky（ <a href="mailto:meghan.bobrowsky@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">meghan.bobrowsky@wsj.com</a> ）和 Alyssa Lukpat（ <a href="mailto:alyssa.lukpat@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">alyssa.lukpat@wsj.com</a> ）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 23:49:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musk-twitter-x-rebrand-trademark-bird-logo-b7433fb6</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musk-twitter-x-rebrand-trademark-bird-logo-b7433fb6<author><![CDATA[Talal AnsariMeghan BobrowskyAlyssa Lukpat]]></author><category> WSJSpeeddesk</category><category>社交媒体</category><category>社交网络</category><category>推文</category><category>市场研究/公共关系</category><category>公共关系</category><category>广告/营销/公共关系</category><category>商业/消费者服务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>社交媒体平台/工具</category><category>技术</category><category>企业犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>知识产权</category><category>工业产权</category><category>商标</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>色情</category><category>社会问题</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>社交媒体</category><category>推文</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>特斯拉</category><category>特斯拉</category><category>元平台</category><category>梅塔</category><category>埃隆·马斯克</category><category>企业犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>知识产权</category><category>工业产权</category><category>商标</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>犯罪</category><category>色情</category><category>社会问题</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>市场调查</category><category>公共关系</category><category>广告</category><category>营销</category><category>商业</category><category>消费服务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体</category><category>娱乐</category><category>社交媒体平台</category><category>工具</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Businesses Look Beyond the Cloud to Run Software]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>当与云的连接不可用或不切实际时，一种利用蓝牙和来自移动设备的其他无线电信号的新型迷你网络可以让企业保持数据流动<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001088010"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824559?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">阿拉斯加航空公司部署了软件，使空乘人员能够在空中更轻松地共享数据。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：约书亚·罗伯茨/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001088010"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/angus-loten" itemprop="url" rel="author">安格斯·洛滕</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 26 日晚上 7:37 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/businesses-look-beyond-the-cloud-to-run-software-23a67e3"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>直到去年，阿拉斯加航空公司的空乘人员几乎没有工具可以相互沟通并跟踪膳食、饮料和其他乘客服务。</p><p>最好的情况是，他们有机载电话，可以将信息从机舱前部传递给后部的机组人员。他们无法访问现代软件来帮助管理这些任务，因为网络连接的选项有限。卫星通信不稳定，安装专用通信服务器会占用太多宝贵的空间。</p><p>去年秋天，随着该航空公司开始推出一种新形式的机载通信网络，该网络采用蓝牙和来自员工移动设备的其他无线电信号，这种情况开始发生变化。总部位于旧金山的 Ditto 软件现已全面部署，允许乘务员在空中使用各种应用程序，并在返回地面后与云计算平台同步数据。</p><p>阿拉斯加航空公司产品管理、设计和软件工程总经理帕特里克·奥布莱恩表示，这些网络允许乘客服务数据在空乘人员之间实时共享。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="639" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824624?width=639&amp;height=639" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Patrick O&#39;Brien，阿拉斯加航空公司产品管理、设计和软件工程董事总经理。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：阿拉斯加航空</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>以前，在机舱后部为乘客提供服务的空乘人员可能不知道前部存储的菜单项何时用完。奥布莱恩说，现在，“他们只需在送餐后刷卡即可，所有其他服务员都会收到通知。”</p><p>尽管云计算近年来蓬勃发展，但在航空旅行等情况下，持续连接到云仍然很困难。在其他情况下，与云的持续连接可能并不可取，因此需要使用所谓的云可选系统（例如 Ditto）。</p><p> IT 研究和咨询公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/IT" class="">Gartner</a>的高级总监分析师 Sandeep Unni 表示，离线销售点应用程序在零售商中越来越受欢迎，店内员工的移动设备充当处理和应用生成数据的中心<span class="company-name-type">。</span>市场上的供应商包括 Ditto、Aptos 和 ObjectBox。</p><p> Unni 表示，将大量数据发送到云端，然后再返回给需要的员工，“不仅会影响性能和延迟，还会增加零售商持续的云计算成本。”</p><p>迈克·休斯，</p>零售软件制造商 Aptos 的副总裁表示，即使高速互联网和蜂窝网络的可用性不断增加，许多零售商的商店中仍然存在“死角”，或者商店位于信号接收不稳定的区域。<p></p><p>休斯说：“对于任何零售商来说，最可怕的情况之一就是无法完成交易，从而导致销售损失和客户不满。” “如果该设备只能在连接到云端时使用，”他说，“它就会变成一个昂贵的镇纸。”休斯表示，至少有十几家大型零售商正在使用 Aptos 新销售点软件的最新版本。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> Ditto 首席执行官兼联合创始人 Adam Fish 表示：“零售业对我们来说是一个巨大的空间。” “这些机构的运营商不关心云或数据中心。他们刚拿到货，就想把顾客推出去，”他说。</p><p>今年 4 月，Chick-fil-A 开始使用 Ditto 的云可选销售点系统。它将餐厅工作人员的智能手机连接到本地网络，在点餐员、厨房工作人员和取餐柜台之间共享信息，而无需从云端来回传输数据。</p><p>这加快了订单履行速度，更重要的是，可以保护运营商免受失去互联网连接的风险。</p>克里斯·泰勒（Chris Taylor）是亚特兰大连锁餐厅的客户技术解决方案高级总监。<p></p><p> “对失去连接的恢复能力一直是我们的北极星，”泰勒说。 “我们的餐厅团队成员应该能够接受订单、接受订单付款以及在有或没有云访问的情况下履行订单。”</p><p>写信给安格斯·洛滕 (Angus Loten)： <a href="mailto:Angus.Loten@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Angus.Loten@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 23:37:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/businesses-look-beyond-the-cloud-to-run-software-23a67e3</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/businesses-look-beyond-the-cloud-to-run-software-23a67e3<author><![CDATA[Angus Loten]]></author><category>计算机/消费电子产品</category><category>Networking</category><category>零售批发</category><category>航空公司</category><category>计算机服务</category><category>航空运输</category><category>云计算</category><category>商业/消费者服务</category><category>数据服务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>技术</category><category>运输/物流</category><category>Wireless Area Network Technology</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>电脑</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>networking</category><category>零售</category><category>批发的</category><category>航空公司</category><category>计算机服务</category><category>航空运输</category><category>云计算</category><category>商业</category><category>消费服务</category><category>数据服务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>技术</category><category>运输</category><category>logistics</category><category> wireless area network technology </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meta Takes Some Profitable Social Cues]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Facebook parent&#39;s strong results and outlook set a better stage for investment cycle <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001087817"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="572" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823961?width=860&amp;height=572" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Meta&#39;s Mark Zuckerberg learned from the brutal selloff that followed his first run at the metaverse.</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：大卫·保罗·莫里斯/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001087817"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dan-gallagher" itemprop="url" rel="author">丹·加拉格尔</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">July 26, 2023 7:06 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/meta-takes-some-profitable-social-cues-ca2eb3ae"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Facebook&#39;s parent company has a history of testing its friendships. At least it has picked a much better time to do it.</p><p> The company now known as <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/META" class="company-name">Meta Platforms</a> faced a high bar with its <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/meta-platforms-facebook-q2-earnings-report-2023-a0297b9c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">second-quarter results</a> on Wednesday. Its stock price had more than doubled since the start of the year—the second-best performance in the entire S&amp;P 500. Fortunately, those results delivered, with advertising revenue, user growth and an outlook that all exceeded Wall Street&#39;s expectations. Meta&#39;s stock jumped 7% in after-hours trading following the report. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824596?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> Investors aren&#39;t Facebook&#39;s only friends. The company added 27 million daily active users to the flagship social-networking app during the quarter, which was more than twice the number analysts had expected. It expanded its total daily user base for its family of apps by about 50 million during the period—even before it launched a rival Twitter-like app called Threads earlier this month.</p><p> That effort isn&#39;t producing any revenue yet, nor does the company&#39;s management expect it to do so for the foreseeable future. But Meta can afford to play in the microblogging space—especially with <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/elon-musk">Elon Musk</a> well on his way to torching the business he dropped $44 billion on last year. Meta&#39;s latest results come two days after Musk <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musk-twitter-x-rebrand-trademark-bird-logo-b7433fb6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">rebranded Twitter</a> as X as part of a stated desire to build a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-everything-app-delusion-11665185503?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">“super app”</a> that would combine disparate activities such as social networking and banking. Advertisers that once supported the platform don&#39;t seem enthused; The Wall Street Journal reports that X is now offering <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musks-rebranded-twitter-cuts-ad-prices-d2615d8f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">50% discounts</a> to advertisers to lure them back. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=37245C31-BAF7-4987-B2C1-BA54167C5088&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fmeta-takes-some-profitable-social-cues-ca2eb3ae&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Facebook 母公司 Meta 推出了 Threads，这是一款独立的微博应用程序，可与埃隆·马斯克 (Elon Musk) 的 Twitter 相媲美。 Within seven hours of its launch, the app gained 10 million sign-ups, according to Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg. Photo: Yui Mok/ZUMA Press<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Meta is having no such troubles. The company&#39;s ad revenue jumped 12% year over year to $31.5 billion for the second quarter, beating Wall Street&#39;s projections by 4%. Meta projected total revenue growth at a midpoint of 20% year over year for the third quarter compared with the 13% growth Wall Street had been expecting.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> The company once punished by investors for a puzzling pivot to the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/facebook-meta-virtual-reality-metaverse-11665087982?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">so-called metaverse</a> clearly feels it has regained enough goodwill to power another sort of investment phase. Meta said Wednesday that it expects capital expenditures to grow in 2024 compared with a small decline expected for this year as it works to build more generative artificial- intelligence capabilities into its networks. It expects operating losses in its Reality Labs division that houses much of its metaverse efforts to grow meaningfully in 2024. That unit has run up more than $15 billion in losses over the past four quarters.</p><p> But core operating margins of the company&#39;s advertising business are now back above 40%—up 6 percentage points from six months ago. Chief Executive Officer <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/mark-zuckerberg">Mark Zuckerberg</a> clearly got the message from the brutal selloff that followed his first run at the metaverse. “I&#39;m going to be focused on continuing to run the company as lean as possible for these cultural reasons even though our financial results have improved,” he said on Wednesday&#39;s call, adding that Threads was built “by a relatively small team on a tight timeline.”</p><p> Zuck&#39;s effort at <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/jiu-jitsu-mark-zuckerberg-9aff7dc1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">bulking himself up</a> seems to have driven home the benefit of keeping the fat to a minimum.</p><p id="correction" class="correction"><strong>更正和放大</strong><br>Twitter was rebranded as X two days earlier. An earlier version of this article incorrectly said that Twitter was renamed as X Corp. two days earlier. The company was renamed in April. （7月26日更正）</p><p>写信给 Dan Gallagher： <a href="mailto:dan.gallagher@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dan.gallagher@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/d90969df-db3f-4890-9f4e-2892f502493a.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 23:06:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/meta-takes-some-profitable-social-cues-ca2eb3ae</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/meta-takes-some-profitable-social-cues-ca2eb3ae<author><![CDATA[Dan Gallagher]]></author><category>市场研究/公共关系</category><category>公共关系</category><category>广告/营销/公共关系</category><category>商业/消费者服务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>社交媒体平台/工具</category><category>技术</category><category>财务绩效</category><category>Earnings</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>元平台</category><category>梅塔</category><category>财务绩效</category><category>收益</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>市场调查</category><category>公共关系</category><category>广告</category><category>营销</category><category>商业</category><category>消费服务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体</category><category>娱乐</category><category>社交媒体平台</category><category>工具</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Hunter Biden Pleads Not Guilty to Tax Charges]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>法官推迟在法庭听证会上考虑认罪协议<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001086059"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=0B3DB0F9-BB08-44C5-9D27-7C99347D4C8F&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fhunter-biden-plea-deal-in-jeopardy-ff556d70&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">照片：安娜·钱梅梅克/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001086059"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sadie-gurman" itemprop="url" rel="author">Sadie Gurman</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/aruna-viswanatha" itemprop="url" rel="author">Aruna Viswanatha</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 26 日下午 5:21（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-plea-deal-in-jeopardy-ff556d70"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>特拉华州威尔明顿——周三，亨特·拜登对税务指控表示不认罪，在法官表示亨特·拜登尚未准备好接受<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-guilty-plea-federal-court-3b15f98b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">他与检察官达成的认罪协议</a>后，情况发生了惊人的逆转。</p><p>在一场持续三个小时的激烈听证会上，拜登总统之子的一名律师最初与检察官就未来指控的可能性发生争执。在双方澄清<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-bidens-messy-path-to-a-plea-deal-c22bd962?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">协议</a>后，美国地区法官玛丽莲·诺雷卡表示，她需要更多信息才能决定是否签署协议。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> “这些协议并不简单，它们包含非典型条款，”她说，并补充道：“我无法决定接受或拒绝认罪协议，我需要推迟它。”</p><p>被前总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">唐纳德·特朗普</a>任命为法官的诺雷卡法官的最后一刻的剧变，标志着司法部对亨特·拜登的财务、商业交易以及有据可查的毒瘾和酗酒成瘾的曲折且具有政治爆炸性的调查的最新转折。</p><p>几周前公开的认罪协议大纲使亨特·拜登有可能将法律麻烦抛在脑后，尽管国会山的共和党人已经升级了对他涉嫌不当行为的听证会和指控，并试图在拜登总统发起<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-touts-job-growth-in-first-re-election-campaign-rally-9337f3c2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">连任竞选</a>时将其与他联系起来。</p><p>检察官保留了未来对亨特·拜登提出指控的可能性，包括与司法部长期以来一直在审查的外国游说法有关的指控。周三的结果意味着他的法律困境仍然存在，并且随着 2024 年竞选活动的推进，可能会为众议院和参议院的共和党人提供新的素材。</p><p>众议院议长凯文·麦卡锡（加利福尼亚州共和党）表示，众议院可能会对拜登总统进行弹劾调查，理由是亨特·拜登的海外商业交易涉及腐败。</p><p>白宫一直表示，拜登总统没有与他的儿子讨论亨特·拜登的商业往来，也没有参与其中。参议院多数党领袖查克·舒默（纽约州民主党人）表示：“我对检方有信心……任何人都不应在政治、意识形态上干涉此事，让正义得以伸张。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824383?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">亨特·拜登在特拉华州威尔明顿举行认罪听证会后离开联邦法院。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔纳森·恩斯特/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>如果负责此案的法官最终不宽恕认罪协议，亨特·拜登将面临目前针对他的指控的审判，就像共和党 2024 年总统候选人领先者特朗普面临司法部<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-indicted-in-document-case-b4e563d7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">指控他处理机密信息不当一样</a>。预计特朗普还将因涉嫌破坏 2020 年大选而被起诉。特朗普否认有任何不当行为。</p><p>小拜登原本预计会承认<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-charged-with-tax-crimes-bd2dea0a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">轻罪税务指控</a>，并已达成协议以避免枪支指控。共和党人指责司法部给予拜登一项宽松的协议，这是其他处于类似情况下的人永远不会得到的。该部门否认有任何偏袒。</p><p>在听证会上，亨特·拜登和他的律师坐在一起，静静地看着诉讼程序展开。他透露了自己的康复情况，并告诉法官，在过去的二十年里，他因吸毒和酗酒至少接受了六次治疗。他说，他最后一次吸毒或酗酒是在 2019 年 6 月。</p><p>白宫新闻秘书卡琳·让-皮埃尔周三下午对记者说：“亨特·拜登是一名普通公民，这对他来说是个人问题。” “正如我们所说，总统和第一夫人，他们爱他们的儿子，并将继续支持他重建生活。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824384?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">执法人员保护了特拉华州威尔明顿联邦法院周围地区的安全。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔纳森·恩斯特/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>这场骚乱始于周三，当时检察官利奥·怀斯坚称对亨特·拜登活动的调查仍在进行中，并在回答法官的问题时表示，他可能面临更多的外国游说指控。</p><p>对此，亨特·拜登的律师克里斯·克拉克表示，他不同意这种解释，并认为该协议排除了额外指控的可能性，并随后补充道：“就我而言，认罪协议是无效的。”</p><p>休会后，亨特·拜登的法律团队表示，该协议涵盖了他在 2014 年至 2019 年期间与税务犯罪相关的责任，并涵盖了毒品和枪支犯罪。法官问亨特·拜登是否曾承诺提供任何其他保护措施来诱使他认罪，他说：“没有，法官大人。”</p><p>然后，法官就协议的两个方面中包含的条款向双方施压，包括为什么税收协议是根据一项取消法院审查能力的法规提出的，而枪支协议则包括要求法院判定亨特·拜登是否违反了协议。诺雷卡法官表示，这可能会让她不恰当地做出通常由检察官做出的决定。</p><p> “我对这项规定的合宪性感到担忧，所以我对这项协议的合宪性感到担忧，”她说。</p><p>法官给了双方 30 天的时间来澄清她的角色并提供更多信息。届时，亨特·拜登可以认罪并将他谈判达成的协议正式化。</p><p>亨特·拜登在听证会结束后走出法院走向一辆等候的SUV时没有发表任何评论。</p><p> On Tuesday, the Republican chair of the House Ways and Means Committee, Rep. Jason Smith (R., Mo.), filed an unusual brief in the case urging the court to consider rejecting the plea deal.它强调了他的小组最近从两名国税局调查员那里听到的证词，称政治考虑可能影响了调查。简报称：“为了所有公民的完全透明和公平，法院掌握这些信息至关重要。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824385?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">共和党众议员贾森·史密斯就亨特·拜登案提交了一份简报，敦促法院考虑拒绝认罪协议。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Rod Lamkey/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>诺雷卡法官表示，她没有时间全面审查这份冗长的申请。</p><p>与联邦检察官达成的协议本应标志着特拉华州美国检察官戴维·韦斯(David Weiss)长达一年的调查的高潮。韦斯是由特朗普任命的，在拜登政府期间一直留任，以彻底完成对总统儿子的刑事调查。作为协议的一部分，检察官同意，只要亨特·拜登保持不吸毒并同意不再拥有枪支，就不会对持有枪支提起单独的重罪指控。</p><p>共和党人承诺继续推进<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-tries-to-end-legal-woes-as-republicans-vow-to-keep-probing-4b6ac7e9?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">自己的调查</a>，旨在通过拜登总统的儿子来污蔑他，并在 2024 年选举周期升温之际让他的麻烦成为焦点。</p><p>众议院监督委员会主席詹姆斯·科默（肯塔基州共和党人）周三表示：“我们将继续追踪拜登父子的资金轨迹。”他赞扬法官“拒绝对这一“甜心交易”盖章。</p><p>民主党人将共和党领导的调查视为政治表演，监督委员会高级成员众议员杰米·拉斯金（马里兰州民主党人）称其为“检查员克鲁索式的对不存在事物的探索”。</p><p>韦斯的办公室同意建议仅缓刑，作为亨特·拜登认罪协议的一部分，但法官拥有最终决定权。亨特·拜登每项罪名最高可被判处 12 个月监禁和 10 万美元罚款。如果亨特·拜登未能兑现不拥有枪支和不吸毒的承诺，枪支指控最高可判处 10 年监禁和巨额罚款。</p><p>该调查于 2018 年开始，首先审查了小拜登的海外商业交易，但近年来，调查重点转向了他的纳税情况以及他在购买枪支表格上的虚假声明，即他没有使用毒品或吸毒成瘾。亨特·拜登在 2021 年的回忆录《美丽的事物》中详细描述了他长期吸毒的情况，并写道，他在 2018 年“每 15 分钟”就抽一根可卡因。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>您认为此案最有趣的是什么？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>韦斯表示，亨特·拜登在2017年和2018年的年收入都超过150万美元，尽管每年欠税超过10万美元，但他没有为此纳税。 《华尔街日报》此前报道称<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/prosecutors-advance-tax-probe-of-hunter-biden-11648465200?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，他偿还了约 100 万美元</a>，而指控称他未能按时支付至少 20 万美元。在检方预计提供更多细节之前，尚不清楚造成这种明显差异的原因。</p><p>根据与枪支指控相关的法庭文件，亨特·拜登在 2018 年 10 月拥有一把柯尔特眼镜蛇 38SPL 左轮手枪，尽管他吸毒成瘾并被禁止拥有枪支。</p><p>这项调查历经两届政府历时五年，并面临许多挑战，包括调查人员之间对如何进行的分歧。到 2022 年中期，调查人员认为有足够的证据来指控亨特·拜登，但<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-case-decision-paused-amid-discussions-between-defense-lawyers-and-prosecutors-11665094544?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">检察官在审查辩方证据时推迟了数月</a>。除其他问题外，检察官还纠结于他的毒瘾是否可以有效地防范潜在的刑事税务案件。</p><p>拜登总统任命司法部长梅里克·加兰（Merrick Garland）的部分原因是他承诺让该部门的调查不受政治影响。他捍卫了调查的独立性，韦斯表示，他被赋予了广泛的自由度，可以在他认为合适的情况下追查此案。</p><p>周一，司法部表示韦斯将在众议院司法委员会作证，并提供了 9 月和 10 月的可能日期，强调他应该在公开听证会上发言，而不是共和党寻求的闭门听证会。</p><p>写信给 Sadie Gurman <a href="mailto:sadie.gurman@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">(sadie.gurman@wsj.com)</a>和 Aruna Viswanatha ( <a href="mailto:aruna.viswanatha@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">aruna.viswanatha@wsj.com</a> )</p><p id="correction" class="correction"><strong>更正和放大</strong><br>亨特·拜登每项罪名最高可被判处 12 个月监禁和 10 万美元罚款。本文的早期版本错误地表示，拜登每项罪名均面临 25,000 美元的罚款。 （7月26日更正）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 21:21:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-plea-deal-in-jeopardy-ff556d70</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-plea-deal-in-jeopardy-ff556d70<author><![CDATA[Sadie GurmanAruna Viswanatha]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>欺诈罪</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>税务欺诈</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>玛丽莲·诺瑞卡</category><category>凯文·麦卡锡</category><category>查克·舒默</category><category>詹姆斯·科默</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>欺诈罪</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>税务欺诈</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Federal Reserve Raises Interest Rates to 22-Year High]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>官员们放慢了今年的增长步伐，但不确定他们是否已完全解决通货膨胀问题<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001086188"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=7E0252B4-152F-44EE-9C61-910343546CB6&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Ffederal-reserve-raises-interest-rates-to-22-year-high-3c3e499c&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">观看美联储主席杰罗姆·鲍威尔的新闻发布会。<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001086188"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/nick-timiraos" itemprop="url" rel="author">尼克·蒂米罗斯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 26 日下午 4:04（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/federal-reserve-raises-interest-rates-to-22-year-high-3c3e499c"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>华盛顿——美联储周三恢复加息，加息幅度为 25 个百分点，这将使利率升至<a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/fed-meeting-interest-rate-decision-today-july-2023?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">22 年来的最高点</a>。</p><p>由于官员们争论是否采取了足够的措施来对抗通胀，上个月一致决定将基准联邦基金利率提高至 5.25% 至 5.5% 的区间，结束了加息<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/fed-holds-rates-steady-but-expects-more-increases-b1be87f2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">的短暂停顿</a>。这是自 2022 年 3 月以来第 11 次加息，当时利率从接近于零的水平上调。</p><p>美联储<a href="https://www.federalreserve.gov/monetarypolicy/files/monetary20230726a1.pdf" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">对其会后声明</a>进行了最小程度的修改，没有就其未来的政策计划提供新的指导。</p><p>在会后的新闻发布会上，美联储主席鲍威尔不排除在央行下次会议上再次加息的可能性，但他强调了央行已经做了多少工作，以及货币政策冷却通胀所需的时间。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>更多关于美联储的信息</h4><ul class="articleList"><li><a href="https://www.federalreserve.gov/monetarypolicy/files/monetary20230726a1.pdf" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">美联储货币政策声明</a></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/fed-meeting-interest-rate-decision-today-july-2023?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">决策后股市动摇</a></li></ul></div></div><p>他说：“当我们让这一切展开时，我们可以保持一点耐心，同时也保持坚决的态度。” “我们认为，当然，我们需要在一段时间内将政策维持在限制性水平，如果我们认为合适，我们将准备进一步加息。”</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/fed-meeting-interest-rate-decision-today-july-2023" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener"><br></a>美联储决定后， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/fed-meeting-interest-rate-decision-today-july-2023" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">市场涨跌互现</a>。</p><p>经济增长可能过于强劲，鲍威尔<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/markets-appear-convinced-the-fed-can-pull-off-a-soft-landing-700a40dd?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">无法像许多投资者预期的那样</a><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/investors-can-read-the-feds-poker-face-a1934d25?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">暗示周三的加息将是当前紧缩周期的最后一次</a>。与此同时，近期通胀放缓可能会减轻央行官员继续加息的压力。</p><p>在六月份的上一次会议上，官员们维持利率稳定，但预计今年还会加息两次。美联储官员计划今年再召开三次会议，下一次会议将于 9 月举行。</p><p>通货膨胀已从去年夏天创下的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-inflation-june-2022-consumer-price-index-11657664129" target="_blank" class="icon none">40 年来的高</a>点回落，6 月份消费者价格指数同比上涨 3%。这远低于 2022 年 6 月 9.1% 的峰值，当时汽油价格达到<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/gasoline-prices-reach-5-a-gallon-nationwide-for-the-first-time-11654910506" target="_blank" class="icon none">每加仑 5 美元的创纪录平均水平。</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=DE0B91C0-D4B9-4619-AFE8-7EA4E62BC84B&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Ffederal-reserve-raises-interest-rates-to-22-year-high-3c3e499c&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> The Federal Reserve is central to the US economy today, but its power has been built over decades. Its decisions can lower inflation or spark a recession. WSJ explains how the Fed was formed and the role it plays. Photo illustration: Annie Zhao<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Fed officials have been concerned that underlying price pressures may prove more persistent as a tight labor market allows workers to bargain for higher pay, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/last-mile-of-the-inflation-fight-will-be-the-hardest-86bcebb1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">making it harder</a> to get inflation down further.</p><p> Core prices, which exclude volatile food and energy categories, posted the smallest monthly gain in more than two years in the June CPI. Still, the core CPI rose 4.8% in June from a year earlier. Until last year, the core CPI hadn&#39;t registered such increases since the early 1990s.</p><p> Fed officials are focused on core inflation because they see it as a better predictor of future inflation than the overall inflation rate.</p><p> The Fed seeks to keep inflation at 2% over time, as measured by its preferred gauge, the personal-consumption expenditures price index. The Fed fights inflation by slowing the economy through raising rates, which causes tighter financial conditions such as higher borrowing costs, lower stock prices and a stronger dollar. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="700" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824356?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> The Fed boosted interest rates aggressively in 2022 and then slowed the pace at the end of the year. Holding rates steady in June offered a way to further dial down the pace of increases and study the effects of those rapid moves, particularly after fears <a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/stock-market-today-dow-jones-05-08-2023/card/banking-stress-a-top-risk-to-u-s-economy-fed-survey-says-tan3K36YS98VljIazfHP?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">&nbsp;</a> that <a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/stock-market-today-dow-jones-05-08-2023/card/banking-stress-a-top-risk-to-u-s-economy-fed-survey-says-tan3K36YS98VljIazfHP?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">banking stress</a> this spring might further constrain credit, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/jerome-powell-says-bank-failures-underscore-need-for-stronger-regulation-supervision-8f386569?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Powell said last month</a> .</p><p> Officials had signaled disagreement in recent months over how quickly to keep raising rates. While all 11 voting members of the policy-setting Federal Open Market Committee agreed to last month&#39;s decision to hold rates steady, some of the 18 voting and nonvoting officials would have supported a rate rise at the June meeting, according to a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/fed-officials-supported-raising-rates-after-june-pause-7b525544?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">written account of the meeting</a> released earlier this month.</p><p> Fed officials meet eight times a year, or roughly twice each quarter. While Powell said last month he wouldn&#39;t rule out raising rates at consecutive policy meetings, he said moving rates up at a slower, quarterly pace could be expected to continue if the economy evolves in line with current expectations.</p><p> A handful of Fed officials, however, have suggested they might prefer to raise rates again at the central bank&#39;s September meeting.</p><p> Fed officials in June raised their projections for interest rates in part because they anticipated less progress on inflation. If inflation continues to cool, that development would raise questions over whether another rate rise later this year will be needed.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>How do you think the Fed should act next?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> Officials who think the impact of the Fed&#39;s rate increases has yet to take full effect are more likely to favor waiting until November or December to decide whether a second interest-rate increase will be appropriate.</p><p> If economic activity slows more by then, officials could decide not to raise rates again and move to a new phase of their tightening campaign—one in which they hold rates steady as inflation slows. That would lead inflation-adjusted, or real, rates to rise higher.</p><p> “For this last part of the tightening cycle, it makes sense to stretch it out over time. They are fine-tuning. They don&#39;t know the exact destination. It makes sense to do that slowly,” said Angel Ubide, head of economic research for global fixed income at Citadel, a hedge-fund firm. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823209?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell didn&#39;t rule out another rate rise at the central bank&#39;s next meeting.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Drew Angerer/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Energy and commodity prices have been responsible for <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/after-global-energy-shock-price-collapse-provides-unexpected-economic-boon-8c2b6660?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">much of the decline</a> in inflation over the past year. A recent upturn in some of those prices could underscore why officials will want to be cautious about assuming further declines in inflation, said Eric Rosengren, who served as Boston Fed president from 2007 to 2021.</p><p> A slowdown in core inflation over the coming months could create a new conundrum for the Fed if officials see reasons to think the improvement will be short lived—for example, because wage growth stays firm. “This is the old, &#39;Be careful what you wish for,&#39;” said Richard Clarida, who served as Powell&#39;s second-in-command from 2018 until January 2022.<br><br> Economists have debated over the past year whether slowing labor demand will require joblessness to rise or whether that can happen as companies reduce vacancies but not head count.</p><p> “A lot of the debate on the labor market is beside the point,” Clarida said. “If I was still over there, what I would worry about is the following: If we don&#39;t get a deceleration in wages and we don&#39;t get a pickup in productivity, then we&#39;re not going to hit our inflation target.”</p><p> Write to Nick Timiraos at <a href="mailto:Nick.Timiraos@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Nick.Timiraos@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 20:04:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/federal-reserve-raises-interest-rates-to-22-year-high-3c3e499c</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/federal-reserve-raises-interest-rates-to-22-year-high-3c3e499c<author><![CDATA[Nick Timiraos]]></author><category> gfx-contrib</category><category>华尔街日报华盛顿</category><category>通货膨胀</category><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>通货膨胀数字/价格指数</category><category>货币政策</category><category>利率</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>Inflation</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Jerome Powell</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>通货膨胀数字</category><category>价格指数</category><category>货币政策</category><category>利率</category><category>经济新闻</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Apps Like Robinhood Make Trading Fun, But SEC Fears It Is Costing Investors]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Regulators consider new limits on apps in wake of meme-stock boom <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001085813"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823536?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> While individual investors tend not to benefit from frequent trading, such behavior can be lucrative for market intermediaries.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Alyssa Schukar for The Wall Street Journal </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001085813"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/paul-kiernan" itemprop="url" rel="author">Paul Kiernan</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated July 26, 2023 2:53 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sec-mulls-new-limits-on-apps-that-use-data-to-make-stock-trading-fun-674abf3c"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> WASHINGTON—Federal regulators want to impose new guardrails on the way retail investment firms such as <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/HOOD" class="company-name">Robinhood Markets</a> use advanced analytics to encourage customers to trade, the latest in a series of policy efforts prompted by <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-rise-and-fall-of-the-gamestop-frenzy-11613083164?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the 2021 meme-stock craze</a> .</p><p> The Securities and Exchange Commission voted 3-2 Wednesday to propose a rule that would hold algorithms that predict, guide or forecast investors&#39; behavior, in certain cases, to a similar standard as investment advice. It would require brokers and advisers who deploy such tools to “neutralize or eliminate” conflicts of interest they create.</p><p> The agency&#39;s goal is to prevent emerging technologies from undermining firms&#39; legal obligation to act in the best interests of their clients.</p><p> “Members of the public know some forms of these predictive data analytics well: The flashing button on your screen, the push notification, the colors, the sounds,” SEC Chair Gary Gensler said. He said investors should be protected from conflicts of interest “even in instances when those interactions may not amount to providing advice or recommendations.”</p><p> The SEC&#39;s two Republican commissioners voted against the proposal, saying it could hamper innovation. One of them, Mark Uyeda, described it as “breathtakingly broad in its reach.”</p><p> Robinhood said the SEC&#39;s proposal threatened to undo the progress that the company had made over the past decade in broadening access to investing through its popular app.</p><p> “The SEC&#39;s proposal would turn back the clock, bringing US financial markets to the old, manual days when retail investors were forced to interact with their broker or advisor by phone or at a branch office. This isn&#39;t in anybody&#39;s best interest, least of all the new generation of retail investors,” Robinhood Chief Brokerage Officer Steve Quirk said.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>Should US regulators have more say over how Wall Street firms use notifications, gamelike features and algorithms on their retail investment platforms?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> The rule proposal stems from a two-year SEC review of Wall Street&#39;s “digital engagement practices” following the trading frenzy in <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GME" class="company-name">GameStop</a> and other meme stocks in early 2021. That episode sparked <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/robinhood-citadel-others-prepare-for-the-gamestop-spotlight-in-washington-11613655854?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">congressional hearings</a> , a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/gamestop-trading-frenzy-tested-resilience-of-markets-sec-says-11634589000" target="_blank" class="icon none">45-page SEC staff report</a> and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sec-set-to-propose-rules-that-would-squeeze-stock-market-middlemen-11671033619" target="_blank" class="icon none">sweeping proposals</a> to change the way stock trading works behind the scenes.</p><p> Regulators worried that by <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/robinhood-day-trade-i-started-trading-hot-stocks-then-i-couldnt-stop-11607095765" target="_blank" class="icon none">bombarding investors</a> with push notifications, colorful graphics and gamelike features, brokerage apps could induce users to trade too much for their own good. While individual investors tend not to benefit from frequent trading, such behavior can be <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/payments-to-u-s-brokers-surged-amid-meme-stock-and-options-boom-11643745771" target="_blank" class="icon none">lucrative for market intermediaries</a> .</p><p> Existing SEC rules prohibit retail brokers from putting their own financial interests ahead of their customers&#39; when making investment recommendations. Rather than simply urging clients to pile into products that generate the highest commissions or fees, a broker must take into account things such as the investor&#39;s risk tolerance, liquidity needs and investment time horizon.</p><p> Traditionally, that advice came when an investor called up a broker, who made suggestions about what stocks to buy. But regulators say investment advice has changed with the growth of self-directed platforms that operate primarily over the internet. After the GameStop day-trading craze, they questioned whether trading platforms&#39; use of engaging features—such as a list of “top mover” stocks—might function as a recommendation.</p><p> The proposal Wednesday would expand the SEC&#39;s oversight of broker and adviser conduct beyond outright recommendations.</p><p> It would apply to any analytical tools used by investment firms to predict or direct investment-related behaviors. Whenever such a “covered technology” takes the firm&#39;s own interest into consideration in interactions with investors, a conflict of interest would exist under the proposed rule. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824028?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The proposal Wednesday would expand the Securities and Exchange Commission&#39;s oversight of broker and adviser conduct beyond outright recommendations.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Ting Shen for the Wall Street Journal</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Brokers and advisers would have to determine whether such conflicts could result in their interest being placed ahead of their customers&#39; and eliminate such effects. They would also have to develop written policies and procedures outlining how they would comply with the requirements.</p><p> The SEC will seek public comment for at least two months before beginning work on a final rule.</p><p> “I think the SEC is trying to fill what it views as a gap,” said Zachary Zweihorn, a partner at Davis Polk &amp; Wardwell who focuses on broker-dealer regulation. “Firms might use these technologies in interactions with customers, even in interactions that potentially &#39;guide&#39; investor behavior, but not in a way that constitutes a &#39;recommendation&#39; as that term has been interpreted.”</p><p> Uyeda, the GOP commissioner, said he fears technologies as simple as electronic calculators or tools that calculate an investor&#39;s future retirement assets could be covered.</p><p> “Virtually any investor interaction that is not purely administrative appears to be covered,” Uyeda said.</p><p> Stephen Sikes, chief operating officer of investment platform Public, said the industry needs guidelines to prevent abuses of newer technologies but “rules that are vague or over-inclusive will chill innovation in our space and ultimately harm customers.”</p><p> Also on Wednesday, the SEC voted 3-2 to adopt a separate rule <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sec-considers-rule-requiring-firms-to-report-cyber-attacks-within-four-days-11646838001?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">proposed last year</a> that requires publicly traded companies to disclose major cybersecurity breaches to their investors. Companies will have to file an 8-K form within four business days of determining that a cyber incident is significant to investors. They can extend that time frame if the US attorney general deems that immediate disclosure would pose a risk to national security or public safety.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Hannah Miao and Alexander Osipovich contributed to this article.</p><p> Write to Paul Kiernan at <a href="mailto:paul.kiernan@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">paul.kiernan@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 18:53:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/sec-mulls-new-limits-on-apps-that-use-data-to-make-stock-trading-fun-674abf3c</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/sec-mulls-new-limits-on-apps-that-use-data-to-make-stock-trading-fun-674abf3c<author><![CDATA[Paul Kiernan]]></author><category>金融投资服务</category><category>Security Brokering/Dealing</category><category>金融服务</category><category>Investing/Securities</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Investment Ideas/Investor Education</category><category> Personal Finance</category><category> Personal Investments</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Robinhood Markets</category><category> HOOD</category><category> GameStop Cl A</category><category> GME</category><category> Steve Quirk</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>investment ideas</category><category> investor education</category><category> personal finance</category><category> personal investments</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>金融投资服务</category><category>security brokering</category><category> dealing</category><category>金融服务</category><category>investing</category><category> securities </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Automakers Plan Thousands of EV Chargers in U.S. Push]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> GM, Honda and Stellantis are among the companies investing in charging joint venture <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001085874"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="627" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824045?width=860&amp;height=627" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A lack of charging stations is cited by US consumers as a top concern keeping them from switching to an EV.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Walt Unks/Associated Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001085874"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/mike-colias" itemprop="url" rel="author">Mike Colias</a></span> , <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/river-davis" itemprop="url" rel="author">River Davis</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ryan-felton" itemprop="url" rel="author">Ryan Felton</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated July 26, 2023 2:33 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/big-automakers-plan-thousands-of-ev-chargers-in-1-billion-u-s-push-af748d19"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> A group of major automakers is planning a joint investment to build thousands of electric-vehicle chargers in the US, in a bid to ease <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ev-charging-service-mobile-432572f2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a shortage of charging spots</a> that deters many consumers from choosing EVs.</p><p> The companies— <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/XE/XETR/BMW" class="">BMW</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> General Motors, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/HMC" class="">Honda Motor</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> Hyundai Motor, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/KR/XKRX/000270" class="">Kia</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> Mercedes-Benz and Jeep maker <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/STLA" class="company-name">Stellantis</a> —plan to collectively invest at least $1 billion in a joint-venture company that will build out charging stations, people familiar with the plan said. The group is targeting the addition of around 30,000 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/faster-ev-charging-stations-eaf60514?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">fast chargers</a> in urban and highway areas over several years, the companies confirmed Wednesday after The Wall Street Journal reported details of the plan.</p><p> The companies said the chargers would be available to all EV drivers, with the first ones operational by mid-2024.</p><p> The joint investment is modeled after a similar charging company in Europe, Ionity, that was formed in 2017, funded by many of the same automakers.</p><p> Those automakers and others are rushing to develop more electric cars, and have laid out plans to convert much of their vehicle lineups to EVs in coming years. <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ev-charging-stations-electric-vehicles-11669737656?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">A lack of charging stations</a> is cited by US consumers as a top concern keeping them from switching to an electric vehicle, surveys have shown.</p><p> Carmakers in recent weeks have disclosed <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ford-taps-teslas-superchargers-network-stirring-debate-on-ev-charging-standard-3ed1a370?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a string of moves</a> to give current and future EV customers more places to power up. <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GM" class="">General Motors</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> Mercedes, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/F" class="">Ford Motor</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NSANY" class="company-name">Nissan Motor</a> and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/RIVN" class="company-name">Rivian Automotive</a> have made deals with EV leader <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TSLA" class="company-name">Tesla</a> for partial access <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/gm-ev-owners-to-tap-teslas-supercharger-network-541f5beb?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">to the company&#39;s US system</a> of about 22,000 fast chargers, known as its Supercharger network.</p><p> Those automakers also plan to switch to Tesla-style charging hardware on their EVs within a few years, from a different format used today by nearly all major car companies.</p><p> The new company being created by the seven automakers plans to install a combination of each type of charger—Tesla&#39;s, known as the North American Charging Standard, or NACS; and the Combined Charging System, or CCS, used by other car companies. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=3F1DA9CD-4380-40E6-8861-82B1288F033F&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fbig-automakers-plan-thousands-of-ev-chargers-in-1-billion-u-s-push-af748d19&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Could Tesla&#39;s charger become the US standard for EV charging? WSJ&#39;s George Downs explores the challenges facing America&#39;s charging network and what funding is up for grabs. Illustration: George Downs<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>With a number of automakers now vowing to eventually migrate to <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/rivian-to-use-teslas-ev-charging-standard-f04eae51?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the same charging port that Tesla uses</a> , that hardware is likely to emerge as the industry standard, auto executives and analysts say. Still, CCS chargers are likely to stick around in the US for a decade or longer, because hundreds of thousands of EVs with that hardware already are on the road, with more coming.</p><p> Tesla began constructing its Supercharger network more than a decade ago, and it has grown into the industry&#39;s largest. The network, considered a major selling point for Tesla customers, accounts for about 60% of all the fast chargers in the US, according to the Energy Department.</p><p> Most of the others are owned or operated by third-party charging companies such as Electrify America, ChargePoint and EVgo.</p><p> The US will need an influx of fast chargers to support the expected surge in plug-in vehicles on the road. Citing data from the federal National Renewable Energy Laboratory, the group of seven automakers said 182,000 fast chargers will be needed nationwide by 2030, up from around 32,000 today.</p><p> Traditional automakers for years were reluctant to invest directly in charging stations. But that has changed in the past few years as EV adoption becomes critical to their business strategies. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="453" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824040?width=700&amp;height=453" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Tesla&#39;s Supercharger network accounts for about 60% of all the fast chargers in the US</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: saul loeb/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p></p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MBGYY" class="company-name">Mercedes</a> plans to <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/mercedes-benz-plans-to-install-its-own-network-of-ev-chargers-11672944214?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">install 10,000 high-powered fast chargers</a> globally over several years, including about 3,000 in North America, the company said early this year. General Motors in 2021 outlined plans to spend $750 million on chargers in North America, although its recent Tesla deal will allow it to forgo some of that spending, the company said.<p></p><p> Individually, the investments into the new charging JV by the seven automakers—which are to be made in equal contributions, the people familiar with the plans said—amount to relatively minor capital investments for companies with multibillion-dollar annual capital budgets.</p><p> The automakers backing the charging venture are hoping others will join and invest in the company following its launch.</p><p> There is precedent in the car business for rival automakers to cooperate on projects, sometimes to defray capital costs, or to share the risk of unproven technologies.</p><p> GM and Honda have co-invested in GM&#39;s majority-owned Cruise autonomous-vehicle company, for example. Mercedes, BMW and Audi jointly own a digital-map provider.</p><p> Write to Mike Colias at <a href="mailto:mike.colias@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">mike.colias@wsj.com</a> , River Davis at <a href="mailto:river.davis@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">river.davis@wsj.com</a> and Ryan Felton at <a href="mailto:ryan.felton@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ryan.felton@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 18:33:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/big-automakers-plan-thousands-of-ev-chargers-in-1-billion-us-push-af748d19</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/big-automakers-plan-thousands-of-ev-chargers-in-1-billion-us-push-af748d19<author><![CDATA[Mike ColiasRiver DavisRyan Felton]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>机动车</category><category>Passenger Cars</category><category> Sports Utility Vehicles</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>Audiovisual Production</category><category> Television Program Production</category><category>汽车</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>Corporate Strategy/Planning</category><category>所有权变更</category><category>Joint Ventures/Consortia</category><category> Capacity/Facilities</category><category>企业行动</category><category>Capital Expenditure</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Honda Motor</category><category> 7267.TO</category><category> JP:7267</category><category> General Motors</category><category> GM</category><category> Mercedes-Benz Group</category><category> MBG.XE</category><category> XE:MBG</category><category> Kia</category><category> 000270.SE</category><category> KR:000270</category><category> Rivian Automotive Cl A</category><category> RIVN</category><category> Stellantis NV</category><category> STLAM.MI</category><category> STLA</category><category> Bayerische Motoren Werke</category><category> BMW.XE</category><category> XE:BMW</category><category> corporate strategy</category><category> planning</category><category>所有权变更</category